content.description: Start on horizontal rail, head over the lip and exit to the right on mossy goodness. Would be better if it were cleaner, bring a big brush.
content.location: Right most problem on the boulder.

content.description: Stand start in seam underneath the roof. Pull a long move to jugs on the edge of the roof and then follow the crack up and left.
content.protection: Good spotters and pad stacking abilities/don't fall
content.location: Shares the same start as Tin Roof Center underneath the roof.

content.description: The holds on this problem are amazing. Bomber jugs and edges. The movement is also incredible. Long reach back off the start and a super sweet heel hook move after the roof. The landing is a 45 degree slab sloping downhill which makes the problem feel risky. Definitely one of the best that not many know about.
content.location: Stand start in seam underneath the roof. Work out of the roof on jugs and head straight up.

content.description: Squat start with good hands in the crack. Work upwards on good sidepulls to gain the lip. Hidden crack makes topping a breeze.
content.protection: Full pad with a spotter to ensure you don't get wet.
content.location: Below the Tin Roof Boulder, moving down towards the river, it will be on your right side. On a ledge over the river.

content.description: This boulder is secluded and in an area of dense tree cover. It would be a great place to climb when it's warm to escape the heat. The landing is not ideal and is difficult to protect. If you want to climb the problems on this boulder, spotters are recommended.
